The bells are ringing for this cover of the "Fairytale Of New York". Ed Sheeran and Anne-Marie reworked The Pogues' and Kirsty MacColl's classic 1988 Christmas track for BBC Radio 1's Live Lounge on Tuesday, and they didn't disappoint fans with their rendition: The pair also treated listeners to an updated version of another holiday track at the end of their performance. Check it out above, and see how it compares to the original below: